---
import Base64Tool from "./Base64Tool.astro";
import JsonFormatterTool from "./JsonFormatterTool.astro";
---

<div class="bg-neutral-900 py-10 lg:py-16" id="projects">
  <div class="max-w-5xl px-4 xl:px-0 mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-10 lg:mb-14">
      <h2
        class="text-white font-semibold text-2xl md:text-4xl md:leading-tight"
      >
        Interactive Tools & Mini Projects
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-neutral-400">
        Here’s a peek at some of the things I’ve been building lately—projects
        that kept me up late (in a good way) and taught me a ton along the way.
        A few small tools I've built to experiment and showcase different
        functionalities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 lg:gap-8">
      <a
        href="/base64"
        class="block p-6 bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-700 transition"
      >
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">
          Base64 Encoder / Decoder
        </h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
          Quickly encode or decode text to/from Base64, plus URL-safe variants.
        </p>
      </a>
      +
      <a
        href="/json-formatter"
        class="block p-6 bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-700 transition"
      >
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">JSON Formatter</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
          Paste in raw JSON, validate, format with indentation, and copy the
          result.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
